The recommender system made unsuitable recommendation. 
 Its reasons are as follows: From my self‑introduction I prize intimate, vocal‑forward collections with tight multi‑part vocal interplay, bright/acoustic‑leaning arrangements, warm “human in the room” production, tasteful dynamics, concise sequencing that rewards front‑to‑back listening, and cohesive compilations that feel like a single statement rather than a sterilized, overproduced hits package. I explicitly dislike glossy, overproduced greatest‑hits anthologies and anything that abandons accessible rhythmic guitar arrangements and vocal hooks.
